erändert? Und droht die Ansichtskarte angesichts der Konkurrenz elektronischer Nachfolger auszusterben? Die Beiträger*innen des Bandes gehen diese Fragen unter korpus-, text- und kulturlinguistischen Gesichtspunkten empirisch nach.  afunded by Swiss National Science Foundation (SNSF)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aBild. 4aGermanistik. 4aGruß. 4aKultur. 4aKulturgeschichte. 4aLiteratur. 4aLiteraturwissenschaft. 4aMedien. 4aPostkarte. 4aSprache. 4aSprachwissenschaft. 4aText. 4aTourismus. 4aUrlaub. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aCultural History.  aCulture.  aGerman Literature.  aGreeting.  aHolidays.  aImage.  aLanguage.  aLinguistics.  aLiterary Studies.  aLiterature.  aMedia.  aText.  aTourism.1 aBender, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBubenhofer, Noah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBubenhofer, Noah, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCalleri, Selena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDiekmannshenke, Hajo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGansel, Christina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHausendorf, Heiko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHausendorf, Heiko, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKellenberger, Maaike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoch, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLangenhorst, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 